# Schema-Driven Development

## Schema File Format

Schema files live in `schemas/` (or `examples/`) and define a complete business entity.

```yaml
model: ModelName        # PascalCase Go struct name
table: table_name       # snake_case DB table (auto-derived if omitted)
fields:
  - name: field_name    # snake_case column name
    type: string        # string|text|int|bigint|float|double|decimal|bool|datetime|json|enum
    size: 255           # for string types
    unique: false
    nullable: false
    index: false
    default: "'value'"  # SQL default (quote strings with inner quotes)
    rules: required|email|min:5  # Laravel-style validation
    values: [a, b, c]   # for enum types only

api:
  prefix: /api/v1/items # Route prefix
  actions: [index, show, store, update, destroy]  # CRUD subset
  auth: jwt             # Guard name (empty = no auth)

relations:
  - type: hasMany       # hasMany|hasOne|belongsTo
    model: Related      # Related model name
    fk: custom_fk_id    # Optional custom foreign key
```

## Type Mapping

| Schema Type | Go Type | MySQL | PostgreSQL | SQLite |
|------------|---------|-------|------------|--------|
| string | string | VARCHAR(n) | VARCHAR(n) | VARCHAR(n) |
| text | string | TEXT | TEXT | TEXT |
| int/integer | int | INT | INTEGER | INTEGER |
| bigint | int64 | BIGINT | BIGINT | INTEGER |
| float | float32 | FLOAT | REAL | REAL |
| double/decimal | float64 | DOUBLE/DECIMAL | DOUBLE PRECISION/NUMERIC | REAL |
| bool | bool | TINYINT(1) | BOOLEAN | INTEGER |
| datetime | time.Time | DATETIME | TIMESTAMP | TEXT |
| json | json.RawMessage | JSON | JSONB | TEXT |
| enum | string | VARCHAR(50) | VARCHAR(50) | VARCHAR(50) |

## Generation Output

Running `gai generate --schema schemas/user.yaml` creates:

- `app/models/user.go` — Model struct with orm.Model, fields, relations, tags
- `app/controllers/user_controller.go` — Full CRUD controller with validation
- `database/migrations/<timestamp>_create_users_table.go` — Blueprint migration
- `routes/user_routes.go` — Route registration with auth middleware

## When Editing Schema Types (ai/schema/types.go)

- `GoType()` maps schema type → Go type string
- `NeedsImport()` returns additional import if needed (time, encoding/json)
- Adding a new type requires updating both methods + all 3 driver ColumnType methods

## When Editing Generator Templates (ai/generator/)

- Templates use Go `text/template` syntax
- Model template: `ai/generator/model.go`
- Controller template: `ai/generator/controller.go`
- Migration template: `ai/generator/migration.go`
- Routes template: `ai/generator/routes.go`
- Helper functions: `toSnake()`, `toCamel()`, `pluralize()`, `itoa()` in migration.go
